-- Zimbabwe Wins Toss, Fields Against Sri Lanka in World Twenty20
-- B y   E d i t o r :   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-09-18T13:56:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-18/zimbabwe-wins-toss-fields-against-sri-lanka-in-world-twenty20.html
Zimbabwe won the toss and will
field first against  Sri Lanka  in today’s opening match in
cricket’s ICC World Twenty20 competition.  The Group C game in Hambantota, Sri Lanka, starts at 7:30
p.m. local time (2 p.m. GMT).  Tomorrow Australia plays Ireland in Group B, and
Afghanistan meets  India  in Group A, both games in Colombo.  Defending champion England’s first game in Group A is
against Afghanistan in Colombo on Sept. 21.  The top two in each of the four groups go through to a
Super Eight stage, from which the top two teams in each pool
advance to the semifinals. The final is in Colombo on Oct. 7. 